biome.description: Scorching temperatures, high winds, and low precipitation cause a near-constant cycle of fires to sweep this planet, punctuated by short bursts of lush rebirth between infernos.
Tall, gnarled trees flourish across the surface of this forested world. Sunlight filters past dangling vines, to the saturated undergrowth below.
The strange subversion of photosynthesis that sustains the oddly-hued flora that flourishes on this planet remains an intriguing mystery to Super Earth's greatest exo-biologists.
A blazing-hot desert planet, it's rocky mesas are the sole interruptions to the endless sea of dunes.
Abundant with life, this wet planet is covered in deep oceans, thick forests, and tall grasses.
